    <div class="col-sm-4">
        <h3>What we do</h3>
        <p>
            We develop projects and services to support sustainable and vibrant communities, where people realise their potential and experience a high quality of life. The focus of our activities is on areas where people experience disadvantage.
        </p>
        <p>
            Our approaches are collaborative, challenging and creative. We create a neutral space, where parties can work together on solutions that would be hard to achieve in their own organisations. The Partnership can do this because we are motivated by outcomes and are usually are not linked to any particular approach or solution. We also have good relationships with local players. Partnership people are committed, pro-active and use resources effectively and transparently.
        </p>
        <p>
            Funding for our work comes from a variety of sources; our main funders are the Department of Community, Environment and Local Government and the Department of Social Protection.
        </p>
